filename: Article 10: How BrewNest Handles Lost and Found Items.txt
title: Article 10: How BrewNest Handles Lost and Found Items
paragraph: If a customer leaves a personal item at a BrewNest location, they can call the store directly or email lost@brewnest.eu. Items are kept in a secure box on-site for 14 days before being donated or discarded. For wallets or IDs, staff attempt to contact the owner if details are available. BrewNest is not responsible for lost electronics or valuables left unattended.

filename: Article 1: How to Access Pay Stubs for Employees at BrewNest.txt
title: Article 1: How to Access Pay Stubs for Employees at BrewNest
paragraph:
Employees at BrewNest can access their digital pay stubs through the company's internal HR portal, called NestHR. The portal is available at nesthr.brewnest.eu and requires a company email login. New employees receive their credentials during onboarding.

Pay stubs are uploaded on the 27th of each month, and past records are stored for up to 24 months. If employees forget their password, they can reset it via SMS or by contacting HR directly at hr@brewnest.eu.

In-store team leads can also print pay summaries using the staff tablet under the “Admin Tools” section. Paper copies are no longer distributed starting March 2025.

filename: Article 2: BrewNest Store Hours and Holiday Schedule for 2025.txt
title: Article 2: BrewNest Store Hours and Holiday Schedule for 2025
paragraph: BrewNest cafes are open seven days a week from 7:00 AM to 9:00 PM. Hours may vary slightly by location, especially in shopping malls or transit stations. All locations are closed on December 25 and January 1. On Easter Sunday and Christmas Eve, stores close early at 3:00 PM. The 2025 summer schedule includes extended weekend hours in tourist-heavy cities like Prague and Vienna.

filename: Article 3: How to Apply for a Job at BrewNest.txt
title: Article 3: How to Apply for a Job at BrewNest
paragraph: Interested candidates can apply for a position at BrewNest through the official careers page at careers.brewnest.eu. Applications require a short form, résumé upload, and optional cover letter. Positions range from barista and store manager to corporate roles in marketing and logistics. Applicants are contacted within 7 working days. Internal candidates can apply through NestHR for faster processing.

filename: Article 4: BrewNest Loyalty App: How It Works.txt
title: Article 4: BrewNest Loyalty App: How It Works
paragraph: The BrewNest App is available on Android and iOS and lets customers collect points with every purchase. One point is earned per €1 spent, and 30 points unlock a free drink. The app also includes mobile ordering, exclusive discounts, and a birthday reward. Points expire after 12 months of inactivity. The app can be linked to Google Pay or Apple Wallet for faster checkout.

filename: Article 5: How to Request Time Off as a BrewNest Employee.txt
title: Article 5: How to Request Time Off as a BrewNest Employee
paragraph: Employees request time off using the NestHR portal by navigating to the “Leave & Availability” tab. Requests must be submitted at least 10 days in advance. Approval is typically granted within 3 business days by the team lead or store manager. Emergency leave can be requested by phone or in person. Each employee receives 20 paid leave days per year, prorated by contract length.

filename: Article 6: Wi-Fi and Charging Availability at BrewNest Locations.txt
title: Article 6: Wi-Fi and Charging Availability at BrewNest Locations
paragraph: All BrewNest cafés offer free Wi-Fi with no time limit. The network name is “BrewNest Free” and doesn’t require a password. Power outlets are available at most wall-side tables, but availability may vary by location. Some stores offer USB charging ports near community tables. Customers are encouraged to use headphones in shared spaces for video calls and online meetings.

filename: Article 7: BrewNest’s Refund and Complaint Policy.txt
title: Article 7: BrewNest’s Refund and Complaint Policy
paragraph: If a customer is unhappy with their drink or purchase, they can request a refund or remake at the counter within 15 minutes of purchase. Receipts are required for product returns (e.g., mugs, beans). Formal complaints can be submitted via feedback@brewnest.eu, and all feedback is reviewed within 48 hours. Refunds are issued to the original payment method within 3–5 business days.

title: Article 8: BrewNest Corporate Discount Program
paragraph: BrewNest offers a 10% discount to corporate partners who sign up through the Business Brew program. Companies with over 30 employees can register to receive digital discount cards for staff. The program also includes catering options and early access to seasonal items. To register, HR representatives can contact biz@brewnest.eu with their company name, tax ID, and estimated number of users.

filename: Article 9: Uniform Guidelines for BrewNest Staff.txt
title: Article 9: Uniform Guidelines for BrewNest Staff
paragraph: BrewNest employees are required to wear black pants or jeans, closed-toe shoes, and the official BrewNest shirt provided at onboarding. Aprons and name tags are distributed by store managers. Hair must be tied back, and visible piercings are limited to ears and nose studs. Uniforms must be clean and wrinkle-free. Replacement shirts can be requested once every six months via NestHR.
